About the Atlantic Clipper
Atlantic Clipper is undoubtedly one of the most fun and social tours in the Whitsundays, perfect for the young, young-at-heart, and adventure-driven traveller! If you’re seeking a FUN, SOCIAL, and unforgettable sailing experience around the Whitsunday Islands, the Atlantic Clipper
is the ideal choice.
This 2 day, 2 night sailing tour will take you to explore the stunning Whitsundays, including the breathtaking
, Hill Inlet lookout, and some of the best scuba diving and snorkelling spots in the
Great Barrier Reef Marine Park
True Blue Sailing is famous for offering top-notch trips, thanks to our fun, professional, and friendly crew of up to six members. They are dedicated to ensuring you have the experience of a lifetime! We go above and beyond with waterslides, heated spas, and paddleboards —amenities that set us apart from any other tour in the Whitsundays.
Whether it’s our delicious food, lively banter, exciting water activities, scenic walks, or just having a great time, our crew is committed to making your trip unforgettable.
What Makes the Atlantic CLipper Unique?
Famous for fun, the Atlantic Clipper is the largest sailing boat in the Whitsundays and because of this mega yacht, Atlantic Clipper Overnight Tour boasts unrivalled facilities and water activities that are unmatched by any other boat in the Whitsundays.
21 cabins with air conditioning – a lifesaver in summer! (Cabins range from 2, 3 and 4 beds)
5 heated showers – a treat in the cooler months!
Scuba diving - feel like you are flying into the blue on the best equipped dive boat in the Whitsundays!
Snorkelling - Discover a new world
TWO waterslides - hold on to your bathers as one is a huge 6 metre inflatable!
6 metre dive platform
Freshly prepared breakfast, lunch, dinner and all snacks included (dietaries on request)
BYO alcohol and drinks – we have fridges onboard to keep your drinks nice and cold
Free use of snorkel equipment, stinger suit / wet suit hire and flotation devices
An indoor seating area that can comfortably seat 60 people
A sun tanning deck and sheltered covers at the top – hello bean bags!
A Master Reef Guide to explain the delights of the Great Barrier Reef
Bring your best white outfit for sunset drinks
Atlantic Clipper Whitsundays Itinerary
ALL ABOARD - Meet at Coral Sea Marina, South End.
BAUER BAY – splash about with waterslides & paddleboards
HOOK PASSAGE – we will anchor here for the night
TONGUE BAY – Visit Hill Inlet and Whitehaven Beach
LUNCHEON BAY – Snorkel and scuba dive
LANGFORD ISLAND – Sunset beach party, wear your best white kit
BLUE PEARL BAY – Anchor for the night. Snorkel and scuba dive next morning
This is a sample itinerary of the Atlantic Clipper Overnight Tour. Each tour location is subject to weather conditions. The crew and operations team reserve the right to alter the itinerary at any point to ensure the safety and comfort of our guests.
This action-packed adventure kicks things off in the paradise of Airlie Beach, departing the marina as we set off on an unforgettable sailing experience on the mighty Atlantic Clipper, the Whitsundays largest sailing boat!
As we cruise away from the mainland and sail towards your first stop, we will pass through to Bauer Bay at South Molle Island, here we will let everyone have a swim, play on the waterslides and enjoy the
to get everyone into the tropical holiday vibes. From here we set sail to our anchorage for the night, Hook Passage. Crack open a cold one, kick back and enjoy as you have the best seats in the house for a
over the Whitsunday Islands.
